def plot_sub_sentiment(Airline):
    As= Tweets[Tweets['airline']==Airline]
    count = As['airline_sentiment'].value_counts()
    Index = [1,2,3]
    color=sns.color_palette("viridis_r", 10)
    plt.bar(Index,count,width=0.5,color=color)
    plt.xticks(Index,['Negative','Neutral','Positive'])
    plt.title('Sentiment Summary of' + " " + Airline)

airline_name = Tweets['airline'].unique()
plt.figure(1,figsize=(12,12))
for i in range(6):
    plt.subplot(3,2,i+1)
    plot_sub_sentiment(airline_name[i])

In [162]:
def AIR(Airline):
    airlineName =Tweets[Tweets['airline']==Airline]
    count= airlineName['negativereason'].value_counts()
    Unique_reason= Tweets['negativereason'].unique()
    Unique_reason=[x for x in Unique_reason if str(x) != 'nan']
    Reason_frame=pd.DataFrame({'Reasons':Unique_reason})
    Reason_frame['count']=Reason_frame['Reasons'].apply(lambda x: count[x])
    return Reason_frame

def plot_reason(airline):
    a= AIR(airline)
    count=a['count']
    Id = range(1,(len(a)+1))
    plt.bar(Id,count, color=sns.color_palette("viridis_r", 10))
    plt.xticks(Id,a['Reasons'],rotation=90)
    plt.title('Count of Reasons for '+ airline)
    
plt.figure(2,figsize=(13, 13))
for i in airlines:
    indices= airlines.index(i)
    plt.subplot(2,3,indices+1)
    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.9)
    plot_reason(i)

#visualization using wordcloud for the negative tweets
df=Tweets[Tweets['airline_sentiment']=='negative']
words = ' '.join(df['text'])
cleaned_word = " ".join([word for word in words.split()
                            if 'http' not in word
                                and not word.startswith('@')
                                and word != 'RT'])
wordcloud = WordCloud(stopwords=STOPWORDS,
                      background_color='white',
                      width=3000,
                      height=2500
                     ).generate(cleaned_word)

plt.figure(1,figsize=(12, 12))
plt.imshow(wordcloud)
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()
